President Obama expressed his sadness over the passing of Arthur Sulzberger, who played a significant role in transforming the New York Times into one of the most successful and respected newspapers worldwide. Sulzberger was a strong advocate for a free and independent press that fearlessly seeks the truth, holds those in power accountable, and tells important stories. The President acknowledged Sulzberger's legacy and the impact he had on the newspaper and the journalists he inspired. He extended his thoughts and prayers to Sulzberger's family.